  <para>
    Tests had been run in 2 different environments:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          In a fully controlled VM cluster (Nomer) with the following characteristics:
          <informaltable><tgroup cols="2">
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry><para><emphasis role="strong">Processor</emphasis></para></entry>
                <entry><para>Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5430 @ 2.66GHz</para></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><para><emphasis role="strong">RAM</emphasis></para></entry>
                <entry><para>2GB</para></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><para><emphasis role="strong">Disc space</emphasis></para></entry>
                <entry><para>3.5GB</para></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><para><emphasis role="strong">OS</emphasis></para></entry>
                <entry><para>Linux/gentoo</para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup></informaltable>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          On the uct3-edge cluster of the University of Chicago, also used by other users,
          with the following characteristics:
          <informaltable><tgroup cols="2">
